  "prompt": "Is there a way to sort by the most upvoted answers on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Quora does not have a built-in feature that allows users to sort answers specifically by the number of upvotes. However, you can sort answers by \"Most Relevant\" or \"Recent,\" which might include highly upvoted answers in the relevant results. \n\nTo find the most upvoted answers, you could also look for answers that have been highlighted or featured by Quora, as those often tend to be well-received by the community. Additionally, you can check for answers that have a high number of upvotes in their summary or preview directly in the feed.\n\nAlways check the Quora platform for the latest updates and features, as they may introduce new sorting options or functionalities.",
